article.headline: VCU 75, Northeastern 65
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Rob Brandenberg scored 16 of his 19 points in the second half and Treveon Graham had 10 of his 16 after the break Saturday night, leading Virginia Commonwealth to a 75-65 victory against Northeastern in the Colonial Athletic Association quarterfinals. Bradford Burgess added 10 points as the second-seeded Rams (26-6) won for the 23rd time in their last 26 games. They forced 25 turnovers that turned into 25 points -- including 16 points in the second half as their pressure defense helped them escape a 26-all tie at the intermission. Joel Smith and Quincy Ford led the Huskies (14-17) with 17 points each and Jonathan Lee had 16. The Rams, who led by as many as 21, started the second half with a 10-2 burst, and later had an 11-0 run that gave them a 64-43 lead. The Huskies shot 51 percent, but took 12 fewer shots.
